opicID=354.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   summoned armor for pet?</span><hr size=1> Does anyone have any data to support or attack the idea of equipping pet with summoned armor?  That is, while it seems intuitively like a good idea, and the recent verant post seems to support that, I'm wondering if there are any particular down sides, other than the time/mana it costs to summon.<br>
<br>
Phantom leather, elemental defender, spear of warding.  You can outfit a full group of baby vah shir with just these.<br>
<br>
Aanni - mage20 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nickk>Nickk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#333333>(3/12/02 9:19:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: summoned armor for pet?</span><hr size=1> Well,  <br>
<br>
I cast an average DDD (lvl 56 pet) and fully outfitted it from head to flow, and farmed ice giants (all bloody green) in GD for about an hour or two, for quest bits and vendor bait to sell.  <br>
<br>
I watched the fights and armored pet took a lot of hits for only 30dmg.<br>
<br>
now when i lost that pet fighting an Blue giant that was trained from the Giant fort, i summoned a new pet and he took mostly full dmg from melee.  Armored pet ended average fight at 70percent life unarmored pet ended average fight at 40 percent  life.  So just consider summoned gear for pet a very long mana costly investment in a permanent pet ac boost.<br>
<br>
And yes it was confirmed pets use armor when a gm turned one mages pet into a gnome that would show armor equiped.<br>
<br>
Happy huntting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwukongthemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wukong the Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(3/20/02 10:40:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: summoned armor for pet?</span><hr size=1> Do u need give the pet each individual pieces of the armor one at a time or can you give the pet the whole bag in order for the pet to wear armor?<br>
<br>
Wukong <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uraiyaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaiyaEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#333333>(3/21/02 2:51:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: summoned armor for pet?</span><hr size=1> I tried on my pet (lvl49) in DL with armor and without.  I noticed if they have armor, they usually ended up with at least 50% health sometimes 75%, but if they are naked then they are about 20-30% of health left after the fight.  (they are same lvl pets since they are focused and hit for same amount).  So, I'd say yes, pets do wear armors.  I have never tried to give them armor in a bag, I hand it to them 1 by 1. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90395>Raiya</a> / <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90580>Jinling</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uteamnoir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teamnoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#333333>(4/6/02 10:43:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: summoned armor for pet?</span><hr size=1> If you give the bag to a guard, (say, in the bazaar), the guard takes it.<br>
<br>
If you give the guard the pieces one by one, you can see him equip them, one by one.<br>
<br>
I give my pet armor one by one.<br>
<br>
Aanni - now 24. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ushareefrahim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShareefRahim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(4/19/02 10:41:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: summoned armor for pet?</span><hr size=1> Remember, you can give your pet armor pieces 4 at a time. <br>
