<br>
I outfitted it in full summoned gear, including Focus items which we saw it visibly equipped (The Bracer anyway).<br>
<br>
I gave it all of these:<br>
<br>
Suit of Phantom Plate<br>
Ruby Bracelet<br>
Sword of Runes<br>
Elemental Defender (It couldn't dual wield)<br>
Elemental Blanket x 2 (Shoulders/Back)<br>
Shard of the Core<br>
<br>
This thing could solo illis frogs without taking a scratch.  They're arguably the best pets in Sebilis because NPC Fear indoors is just a long duration stun.<br>
<br>
After the pet was released, it nearly took out another group, mostly because it was impossible to land any spells on him (Thanks to having like +50 resists from items). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxantherssb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XantherSSB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(5/17/02 2:38:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   armor for pets</span><hr size=1> The other day myself, and Balhem both epic mages from CT server  dueled in a arena to test this theory about armor.<br>
<br>
We both muzzled,  and BO4 the epic pets.  We chose the epic since we know the pet is the same level every time you make one. Then one pet was plate armored and the other left naked<br>
<br>
After making sure that both pets had cast thier DS we let them fight.  After several run throughs we came to the conclusion that it didnt seem to matter which pet had armor or not.   the fights split evenly at 2 each, and the survivor of the four fights was at around 6 to 9% health each time. <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=0000FF)"><a style="font-family:'tempus sans itc';font-size:120%;font-weight:bold; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=30207>Xanther </a></div><a style="font-weight:bold"<BR>59th Conjurer<BR>
